  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 200C.",
    "Clean and slice the oyster mushrooms into 1/4 inch thick pieces.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat and sauté the shallot and garlic until translucent.",
    "Add the mushrooms and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in the miso paste, smoked paprika, thyme, salt, and pepper, cooking for another minute.",
    "Spread the mushroom mixture evenly over the flatbread sheet.",
    "Sprinkle the grated cheddar cheese on top of the mushrooms.",
    "Bake in the oven for 12 to 15 minutes until the edges are crisp and the cheese is melted.",
    "Remove from the oven, garnish with chopped parsley, slice into squares, and serve warm."
